Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on cryptographic proofs for ensuring existence, integrity, and ownership of data in blockchains.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper addresses scalability and cost-effectiveness in timestamping and anchoring data in blockchains.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with storing and retrieving data in blockchains.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is relevant as the paper discusses certification and verification of data in blockchains.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a method for timestamping and anchoring data in blockchains.
